messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full path
- /api/articles/

All HTTP methods acceptable (overrides others)
- false

Per-method acceptability (based on code)
- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation
- In main (hello.go) the router group v1 is created with r.Group("/api"). Both anonymous and authenticated article routes are registered on v1.Group("/articles"), so the group prefix is "/api" + "/articles". ArticleCreate is registered on its router group as router.POST("/", ArticleCreate), so the full path for that route is "/api/articles/".
- A GET handler is also registered on the same path earlier by ArticlesAnonymousRegister(router.GET("/", ArticleList)). Therefore the path "/api/articles/" has a GET handler (ArticleList) and a POST handler (ArticleCreate).
- No handlers for HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, PUT, DELETE, or PATCH are registered on that path in the provided code, so those methods are marked false. (I did not assume any implicit framework behavior such as automatic HEAD/OPTIONS handling â€” the determination is strictly from explicit route registrations in the code.)
